input_args.passage: 'Rhys ap Tewdwr | Rhys ap Tewdwr (c. 1040 – 1093) was a king of Deheubarth in Wales and member of the Dinefwr dynasty, a branch descended from Rhodri the Great.'
input_args.claim: 'In citation, it is mentioned that the West Saxons, led by Cynegils, defeated the West Britons who were possibly led by Tewdwr ap Peredur at Badbury Rings, Dorset.'
